class Solution {
public:
    string defangIPaddr(string address) {
        string defanged = "";
        for (char c : address) {
            if (c == '.') {
                defanged += "[.]";
            } else {
                defanged += c;
            }
        }
        return defanged;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through each character of the input IP address. If a period is encountered, it appends "[.]" to the result string. Otherwise, it appends the current character. This results in a linear time complexity as it processes each character once. The space complexity is also linear as the output string's size is proportional to the input size.

